<p style="text-align:justify;"><a href="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1966.jpg" target="_blank"><img data-attachment-id="12065" data-permalink="https://blogpackinglight.wordpress.com/2016/12/28/keswick-ccc-campsite/img_1966/" data-orig-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1966.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,900" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="img_1966" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1966.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1966.jpg?w=474&#038;h=356" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-12065" src="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1966.jpg?w=474&#038;h=356" alt="img_1966" width="474" height="356" srcset="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1966.jpg?w=474&amp;h=356 474w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1966.jpg?w=948&amp;h=712 948w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1966.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1966.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1966.jpg?w=768&amp;h=576 768w" sizes="(max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px" /></a>On my recent trip to the Lake District, I stayed at the Keswick C&amp;CC campsite. In the past, I&#8217;ve stayed at the Scotgate campsite in Braithwaite, but I thought I&#8217;d give the Keswick site a go instead. The big advantage of the Keswick site is that it&#8217;s only a short walk into Keswick itself and there&#8217;s a good Booth&#8217;s supermarket close by. It&#8217;s also a bit cheaper than Scotgate if you&#8217;re solo and a C&amp;CC member (which I am).</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><a href="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1970.jpg" target="_blank"><img data-attachment-id="12062" data-permalink="https://blogpackinglight.wordpress.com/2016/12/28/keswick-ccc-campsite/img_1970/" data-orig-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1970.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,900" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="img_1970" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1970.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1970.jpg?w=474&#038;h=356" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-12062" src="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1970.jpg?w=474&#038;h=356" alt="img_1970" width="474" height="356" srcset="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1970.jpg?w=474&amp;h=356 474w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1970.jpg?w=948&amp;h=712 948w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1970.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1970.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1970.jpg?w=768&amp;h=576 768w" sizes="(max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px" /></a>Not surprisingly, it&#8217;s really well setup for camper vans, with excellent hard standing pitches and electric hook ups. There&#8217;s a good amount of space between pitches too. When I was there, there weren&#8217;t many vans, so I could park myself well away from anyone else. The downside was I parked myself well away from the shower block, which was a bit of a mistake!</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><a href="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1988.jpg" target="_blank"><img data-attachment-id="12063" data-permalink="https://blogpackinglight.wordpress.com/2016/12/28/keswick-ccc-campsite/img_1988-2/" data-orig-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1988.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,900" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="img_1988" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1988.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1988.jpg?w=474&#038;h=356" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-12063" src="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1988.jpg?w=474&#038;h=356" alt="img_1988" width="474" height="356" srcset="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1988.jpg?w=474&amp;h=356 474w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1988.jpg?w=948&amp;h=712 948w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1988.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1988.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1988.jpg?w=768&amp;h=576 768w" sizes="(max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px" /></a>The shower block facilities were pretty good, with a good number of shower cubicles, sinks and toilets. A second shower block was closed, but would be needed if the site had more occupants. The facilities were not quite up to the standard of Scotgate, which wouldn&#8217;t shame a hotel. Unlike Scotgate, WiFi is not free and you have to pay extra.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><a href="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1973.jpg" target="_blank"><img data-attachment-id="12067" data-permalink="https://blogpackinglight.wordpress.com/2016/12/28/keswick-ccc-campsite/img_1973/" data-orig-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1973.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,900" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="img_1973" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1973.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1973.jpg?w=474&#038;h=356" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-12067" src="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1973.jpg?w=474&#038;h=356" alt="img_1973" width="474" height="356" srcset="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1973.jpg?w=474&amp;h=356 474w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1973.jpg?w=948&amp;h=712 948w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1973.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1973.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1973.jpg?w=768&amp;h=576 768w" sizes="(max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px" /></a>The camp site is in a wonderful position between the River Greta and the shore of Derwent Water, with beautiful views across the lake towards Borrowdale. The drawback with its position, however, is that there is a risk of flooding. For this reason, vehicles and tents are not allowed to be unattended overnight in case there is a need to evacuate.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">While I can understand this requirement, for me, it&#8217;s a bit of a deal breaker. It would prevent me from doing some backpacking and overnight camping in the fells. This probably means that I&#8217;ll be going back to Scotgate if I want to do backpacking trips. Fortunately, for this trip, I&#8217;d only intended to do a couple of day walks.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;"><a href="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1986.jpg" target="_blank"><img data-attachment-id="12068" data-permalink="https://blogpackinglight.wordpress.com/2016/12/28/keswick-ccc-campsite/img_1986/" data-orig-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1986.jpg" data-orig-size="1200,900" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="img_1986" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1986.jpg?w=300" data-large-file="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1986.jpg?w=474&#038;h=356" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-12068" src="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1986.jpg?w=474&#038;h=356" alt="img_1986" width="474" height="356" srcset="https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1986.jpg?w=474&amp;h=356 474w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1986.jpg?w=948&amp;h=712 948w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1986.jpg?w=150&amp;h=113 150w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1986.jpg?w=300&amp;h=225 300w, https://blogpackinglight.files.wordpress.com/2016/12/img_1986.jpg?w=768&amp;h=576 768w" sizes="(max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px" /></a>The site is open to both camper vans and tents and welcomes backpackers too. The warden and staff were very friendly and helpful. Overall, it&#8217;s a really nice place to stay, just a shame you can&#8217;t leave your van overnight.</p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">More details here: <a href="http://www.campingandcaravanningclub.co.uk/campsites/uk/cumbria/keswick/keswick" target="_blank">Keswick C&amp;CC Campsite</a></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">(Please note there&#8217;s a second, smaller C&amp;CC site next door, <a href="http://www.campingandcaravanningclub.co.uk/campsites/uk/cumbria/keswick/derwentwater" target="_blank">Derwentwater Campsite</a>)</p><br />  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/blogpackinglight.wordpress.com/12061/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/blogpackinglight.wordpress.com/12061/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="https://pixel.wp.com/b.gif?host=blogpackinglight.wordpress.com&#038;blog=2188128&#038;post=12061&#038;subd=blogpackinglight&#038;ref=&#038;feed=1" width="1" height="1" />